*Absolute Function* 

The absolute value is equivalent to a maximum function:

$
  abs(x) = max(x, -x)
$

Thus, it can be linearized when it appears on the smaller side of an inequality:

$
  abs(x) lt.eq y quad arrow.l.r.double.long quad cases(
    x lt.eq y,
    -x lt.eq y,
  )
$

